<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910904-0064</DOCNO><DOCID>910904-0064.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Oracle Systems Corp.:   Financing Talks Extended;   Joint Venture Is Considered</HL><DATE>09/04/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   J.NIP ORCL</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>SOFTWARE (SOF)STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)</IN><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)FAR EAST (FE)JAPAN (JA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Oracle Systems Corp. said it was extending itsnegotiations with Nippon Steel Corp. regarding financingtotaling $200 million.   Oracle, a supplier of database software based in RedwoodShores, Calif., said that the two companies have negotiated&quot;definitive documentation&quot; for the financing, but that&quot;negotiations relating to current or potential overlappingproduct directions have not yet been completed.&quot; Thefinancing is important to Oracle, which ran into financialdifficulties last year because of weak controls and aslowdown in sales.</LP><TEXT>   Nippon Steel, which signed a letter of intent to supplyOracle financing in June, has a software subsidiary in Japanand talks now center on how the two companies can manage ajoint venture in Japan, a spokeswoman for Oracle said.   Oracle also said it has obtained a 30-day extension fromits current banks on its primary credit of $100 million andthat it is negotiating an alternative $100 million creditfacility in case the deal with Nippon Steel is not closed bythe end of the 30-day extension.</TEXT></DOC>